      '[SCD]': 'Sarat Chandra Das’s Tibetan-English Dictionary. The new electronic edition produced by Padma Karpo Translation Committee.',
      '[SGC]': '{yul gangs can pa\'i brda yang dag par sbyor ba\'i bstan bcos kyi bye brag sum cu pa dang rtags kyi \'jug pa\'i gzhung gi rnam par bshad pa mkhas pa\'i mgul rgyan mu tig phreng mdzes shes bya ba bzhugs so/} \'A Beautiful String of Pearls to Adorn the Necks of the Wise, A Thorough Explanation of the Specific Texts The Thirty and Guide to Gender Signs of the Śhāstras that Authentically Set Forth the Signs of the Snowy Land\'. Usually referred to just as {si tu\'i \'grel chen} si tu\'i \'grel chen, Situ’s Great Commentary. The eighth Situ Rinpoche’s great commentary on grammar.',
      '[SNT]': '{phyag chen lnga ldan gyi khrid yig kun mkhyen chos kyi \'byung gnas kyis mdzad pa bzhugs/} \'A Written Instruction on Five-Part Mahāmudrā by All-Knowing Chokyi Jungney\'. By the eighth Situ Rinpoche. Translated by Tony Duff.',
